    "content": "<p>When a simply-supported elastic beam of span L and flexural rigidity EI (E is the modulus of elasticity and I is the moment of inertia of the section) is loaded with a uniformly distributed load w per unit length, the deflection at the mid-span is</p>\n\n<p><span class=\"math-tex\">$\\rm \\Delta_0=\\frac{5}{384}\\frac{wL^4}{El}$</span></p>\n\n<p>If the load on one half of the span is now removed, the mid-span deflection _______.</p>\n",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "reduces to Δ<sub>0</sub>/2&nbsp;"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "reduces to a value less than Δ<sub>0</sub>/2"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "reduces to a value greater than Δ<sub>0</sub>/2"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "remains unchanged at Δ<sub>0</sub>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "explanation": "<p>Given: $\\Delta_0=\\frac{5}{384} \\frac{w L^4}{E I}$</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lzabs2zr/f423179f-4e1f-4725-a68b-98aa334c353b/181a4370-4f7f-11ef-bcd6-9fe42815d370/file-jaoe38c1lzabs2zs.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lzabs2zr/f423179f-4e1f-4725-a68b-98aa334c353b/181a4370-4f7f-11ef-bcd6-9fe42815d370/file-jaoe38c1lzabs2zs.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2023 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 2 English Explanation\">\n\n<p>From above, when load on one half of span is removed, the mid span deflection reduced to $\\frac{\\Delta_0}{2}$.</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
    "answer": null,
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2023-set-2",
    "difficulty": null
  },
