    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>For the beam and loading shown in the figure, the second derivative of the deflection curve of the beam at the mid-point of $A C$ is given by $\\frac{\\alpha M_0}{8 E I}$. The value of $\\alpha$ is _________ (rounded off to the nearest integer).</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbizk7ud/a2799c56-f375-4b4a-be69-edaae36ee8a8/f637ce50-41d4-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbizk7ue.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbizk7ud/a2799c56-f375-4b4a-be69-edaae36ee8a8/f637ce50-41d4-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbizk7ue.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 1 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "3",
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbizkvu0/efa6bd31-82c2-4177-8dcd-21354ddfe8cf/08bfea80-41d5-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbizkvu1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbizkvu0/efa6bd31-82c2-4177-8dcd-21354ddfe8cf/08bfea80-41d5-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbizkvu1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 1 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp;\\text { Let } V_A \\text { and } V_B \\text { be the vertical reactions at } \\mathrm{A} \\text { and } \\mathrm{B} \\text { respectively. }\\\\ &amp;\\begin{aligned} \\Sigma M_A &amp; =0 \\\\ \\left(-V_B \\times 2 L\\right)+M &amp; =0 \\\\ V_B &amp; =\\frac{M_0}{2 L} \\text { and } V_A=\\frac{-M_0}{2 L} \\end{aligned} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>By double integration method, At section $x-x$,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbizmek6/9efe0ad4-e630-4283-9bd6-5c29ac96cd48/33065d60-41d5-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbizmek7.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbizmek6/9efe0ad4-e630-4283-9bd6-5c29ac96cd48/33065d60-41d5-11f0-b55b-2b590ab4dfce/file-jaoe38c1mbizmek7.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 1 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{array}{rlrl} M_0-\\frac{M_0}{2 L} x+\\left[-M_x\\right] &amp; =0 &amp; \\\\ \\text { At } x=\\frac{L}{2} \\quad M_0-\\frac{M_0}{2 L} \\cdot \\frac{L}{2} &amp; =(2 E I) \\frac{d^2 y}{d x^2} \\\\ \\frac{d^2 y}{d x^2} &amp; =\\frac{3 M_0}{8 E I} \\\\ \\Rightarrow  \\alpha  =3 \\end{array} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2025-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
