    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>For the 6m long horizontal cantilever beam PQR shown in the figure, Q is the midpoint. Segment PQ of the beam has flexural rigidity $EI = 2 \\times 10^5$ kN. $m^2$ whereas the segment QR has infinite flexural rigidity. Segment QR is subjected to uniformly distributed, vertically downward load of 5 kN/m. </p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lxt35too/69853d6a-9f92-40a3-b623-4ccb2167d3a2/d9a8c080-3237-11ef-975e-736b2520fa14/file-jaoe38c1lxt35top.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lxt35too/69853d6a-9f92-40a3-b623-4ccb2167d3a2/d9a8c080-3237-11ef-975e-736b2520fa14/file-jaoe38c1lxt35top.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2024 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 3 English\"></p><p>The magnitude of the vertical displacement (in mm) at point Q is _______ (rounded off to 3 decimal places).</p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "1.176TO1.186",
    "explanation": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyk83z7g/c2926a66-9c84-4db2-9da4-9a25fa540990/5d7c9ad0-4124-11ef-8d27-6bea29539b34/file-jaoe38c1lyk83z7h.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyk83z7g/c2926a66-9c84-4db2-9da4-9a25fa540990/5d7c9ad0-4124-11ef-8d27-6bea29539b34/file-jaoe38c1lyk83z7h.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2024 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 3 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>$\\therefore Q R$ will remain straight</p>\n\n<p>[Transferring UDL to point load and moment at Q] From principle of superposition,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyk87hnq/162cea12-79c4-4cf2-af9b-4ce47be586db/bf2adc60-4124-11ef-b088-3bf35da7f3d1/file-jaoe38c1lyk87hnr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyk87hnq/162cea12-79c4-4cf2-af9b-4ce47be586db/bf2adc60-4124-11ef-b088-3bf35da7f3d1/file-jaoe38c1lyk87hnr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2024 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 3 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>Vertical deflection at $Q=\\frac{P l^3}{3 E I}+\\frac{M l^2}{2 E I}$</p>\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_Q=\\frac{(15 \\mathrm{kN})(3 \\mathrm{~m})^3}{3 \\times 2 \\times 10^5 \\mathrm{kNm}^2}+\\frac{(22.5 \\mathrm{kNm}) \\times 3^2}{2 \\times 2 \\times 10^5} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\Delta_Q=\\left(6.75 \\times 10^{-4}+5.0625 \\times 10^{-4}\\right) \\mathrm{m} \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\Delta_Q=1.181 \\mathrm{~mm} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2024-set-2",
    "difficulty": null
