    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The linearly elastic planar structure shown in the figure is acted upon by two vertical concentrated forces. The horizontal beams UV and WX are connected with the help of the vertical linear spring with spring constant k = 20 kN/m. The fixed supports are provided at U and X. It is given that flexural rigidity EI = 10<sup>5</sup> kN-m<sup>2</sup>, P = 100 kN, and a = 5 m. Force Q is applied at the center of beam WX such that the force in the spring VW becomes zero.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0o3okxu/ad8a3cf0-9fe3-44aa-a97e-c5d37ad3f71d/9e2abe20-6ade-11ef-a892-b1dcb62d37bc/file-jaoe38c1m0o3okxv.webp?format=webp\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0o3okxu/ad8a3cf0-9fe3-44aa-a97e-c5d37ad3f71d/9e2abe20-6ade-11ef-a892-b1dcb62d37bc/file-jaoe38c1m0o3okxv.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 4 English\"></p>\n<p>The magnitude of force Q (in kN) is __________. (round off to the nearest integer)</p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "620TO660",
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0ow3dwk/859a76c7-ee50-4d89-a6aa-63e4ada60848/b97c4e40-6b4d-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow3dwl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0ow3dwk/859a76c7-ee50-4d89-a6aa-63e4ada60848/b97c4e40-6b4d-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow3dwl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 4 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; K=20 \\mathrm{kN} / \\mathrm{m} \\\\ &amp; E I=10^5 \\mathrm{kN}-\\mathrm{m}^2 \\\\ &amp; P=100 \\mathrm{kN} \\\\ &amp; a=5 \\mathrm{~m} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Free body diagram,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0ow5rc7/f4eda2db-267c-4f1f-89d5-7789c9482b12/fb7b4b70-6b4d-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow5rc8.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0ow5rc7/f4eda2db-267c-4f1f-89d5-7789c9482b12/fb7b4b70-6b4d-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow5rc8.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 4 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\text { Deflection, } y_1=\\frac{P L^3}{3 E I} \\\\\\\\ &amp; y_1=\\frac{P(2 a)^3}{3 E I} \\\\\\\\ &amp; y_1=\\frac{100 \\times 10^3(10)^3}{3 \\times 10^5 \\times 10^3}=0.333 \\mathrm{~m} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0ow83it/3eb0c428-505d-486c-8be6-69391c24899e/3c82f050-6b4e-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow83iu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0ow83it/3eb0c428-505d-486c-8be6-69391c24899e/3c82f050-6b4e-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow83iu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 4 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0ow98hz/2cf8381c-ce89-449a-b43d-6f23d373b5ff/5c2a4570-6b4e-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow98i0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0ow98hz/2cf8381c-ce89-449a-b43d-6f23d373b5ff/5c2a4570-6b4e-11ef-a23d-0174405e00af/file-jaoe38c1m0ow98i0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Deflection of Beams Question 4 English Explanation 4\"></p>\n<p>By using moment area method</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; y_2=\\frac{1}{2 E I}\\left[\\frac{1}{2} a Q a \\times \\frac{5 a}{3}\\right] \\\\\\\\ &amp; y_2=\\frac{5 Q a^3}{12 E I}=0.33 \\\\\\\\ &amp; 0.33=\\frac{5 Q 5^3}{12 \\times 10^5 \\times 10^3} \\\\\\\\ &amp; Q=640000 \\mathrm{~N}=640 \\mathrm{kN} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2022-set-2",
